WEBVTT



00:00:09.952 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.344 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.888 --> 00:00:25.184
We are continuing our journey through the book of Psalms, and on today's episode, we're excited to have Stephanie Lee reading Psalm 148.

00:00:29.888 --> 00:00:32.128
So i'll be reading psalm 148.

00:00:32.288 --> 00:00:33.536
Praise the Lord.

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:35.392
Praise the Lord from the heavens.

00:00:35.456 --> 00:00:37.408
Praise him in the heights above.

00:00:37.632 --> 00:00:39.712
Praise him, all his angels.

00:00:39.616 --> 00:00:41.856
Praise him, all his heavenly hosts.

00:00:42.016 --> 00:00:44.256
Praise him, son and moon.

00:00:44.512 --> 00:00:46.656
Praise him, all you shining stars!

00:00:46.784 --> 00:00:50.464
Praise him, you highest heavens, and you waters above the skies.

00:00:50.496 --> 00:00:52.608
Let him praise the name of the Lord.

00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:57.568
For at his command they were created, and he established them for ever and ever.

00:00:57.408 --> 00:01:00.256
He issued a decree that will never pass away.

00:01:00.672 --> 00:01:02.432
Praise the Lord from earth.

00:01:02.176 --> 00:01:05.152
You great sea creatures in all of your ocean depths.

00:01:05.376 --> 00:01:08.096
Lightning and hail, snow and clouds.

00:01:07.936 --> 00:01:10.208
stormy winds the dude is bidding.

00:01:10.336 --> 00:01:15.552
You mountains and hills, fruit trees and all cedars, wild animals and all cattle.

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.760
Small creatures and flying birds

00:01:18.048 --> 00:01:19.136
Kings

00:01:19.008 --> 00:01:21.376
All of the Earth and all nations

00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:25.984
You princes and all rulers on earth, young men and women, old men and children.

00:01:26.208 --> 00:01:28.320
Let them praise the name of the Lord.

00:01:28.096 --> 00:01:30.464
For his name alone is exalted.

00:01:30.848 --> 00:01:33.600
His splendor is above the earth and the heavens.

00:01:33.312 --> 00:01:36.064
And he has raised up for his people a horn.

00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:40.768
The praise of all his faithful servants of Israel, the people close to his heart.

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:41.888
Praise the Lord.

00:01:42.304 --> 00:01:43.808
The question is:

00:01:43.584 --> 00:01:48.096
What songs, liturgy, or activities have helped you praise the Lord in the past?

00:01:48.672 --> 00:01:51.616
How can you praise the Lord today like never before?

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:07.616
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:02:07.712 --> 00:02:17.216
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
